        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 1:55PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
west of Kiowa, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Canadian...
Indianola...                      Pittsburg...
Crowder...                        Kiowa...
Haywood...                        Blocker...
Dow...                            Bache...
Arrowhead State Park...           Hartshorne...
Haileyville...                    Featherston...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Krebs...
Alderson...                       Blanco...
Savanna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
